With the Mirror Flats survey on record, the Kiess route-dispatch office now requires the full-route extension through the Glasswind Belt and Tidemouth Dunes to complete the Reach transit certification. Glass scorpion matriarchs have established new breeding positions that block standard observation paths, glassworm tunnel sentinels have sealed off burrowing access to subsurface survey markers, and tidemouth crab broodmothers are disrupting the coastal waypoint installations. Clear one of each to complete the survey.
The full Reach survey from the Mirror Flats to the Tidemouth Dunes is now on record at the Kiess route-dispatch office. Glassworm tunnel access has been restored, scorpion territory boundaries are documented, and the coastal waypoint installations are back in service. The postmaster has dispatched the updated cartographic packet to the Kowloon Jade Clerk commission that co-funded the survey.
